.START 

Odetics Inc. said it received a $14 million contract from Johns Hopkins University, Baltimore, Md., to provide space data-recording systems for future satellite projects. 

The new contract, together with a recent $8 million contract to supply recorders for future space programs, "substantially" increases the company's backlog, said Joel Slutsky, chairman and chief executive officer of the maker of data-collection systems and robotic and artificial intelligence systems. 

